Reconciliation of U.S. Federal Statutory Income Tax Rate to Effective Income Tax Rate
A significant portion of the Company's taxable earnings is generated in the Netherlands. According to Dutch corporate
income tax law, income generated from qualifying innovative activities is taxed at a rate of 7% ("Innovation Box Tax") rather than
the Dutch statutory rate of 25%.  A portion of Booking.com's earnings during the years ended December 31, 2020, 2019 and 2018
qualified for Innovation Box Tax treatment, which had a significant beneficial impact on the Company's effective tax rate for those
years.
